            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">3.501-2</ph> General.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d118e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d120e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
						            Buying-in may decrease competition	or result in poor contract performance. The contracting officer	must take appropriate action to ensure buying-in losses are not	recovered by the contractor through the pricing of-</p>
               <ol id="d118e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d120e16" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
								                Change	orders; or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d120e21" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
								                Follow-on	contracts subject to cost analysis.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d120e26" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
						            The Government	should minimize the opportunity for buying-in by seeking a price	commitment covering as much of the entire program concerned as is	practical by using-</p>
               <ol id="d118e53" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d120e32" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
								                Multiyear contracting, with a	requirement in the solicitation that a price be submitted only for	the total multi-year quantity; or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d120e37" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
								                Priced options	for additional quantities that, together with the firm contract	quantity, equal the program requirements (see <xref href="Subpart_17.2.dita#FAR_Subpart_17_2"
                              base="i1103024"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  17.2</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d120e45" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
						            Other safeguards	are available to the contracting officer to preclude recovery of	buying-in losses (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">e.g.,</i> amortization of nonrecurring costs	(see <xref href="15.408.dita#FAR_15_408"
                        base="i1106593"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15.408</xref>, <xref href="15.408.dita#FAR_15_408/i1106753"
                        base="i1106753"
                        outputclass="fm:Table"
                        class="- topic/xref ">Table  15-2</xref>, paragraph	A, column (2) under "Formats for Submission of Line Item Summaries")	and treatment of unreasonable price quotations (see <xref href="15.405.dita#FAR_15_405"
                        base="i1106373"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15.405</xref>).</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
